couchTests.attachment_sparseness= function(debug) {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;var db = new CouchDB(&quot;test_suite_db&quot;);<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;db.deleteDb();<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;db.createDb();<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (debug) debugger;<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;for (i = 0; i &lt; 1000; i++) {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;var binAttDoc = {<br/>
	  _id: (i).toString(),<br/>
	  _attachments:{<br/>
	      &quot;foo.txt&quot;: {<br/>
		  content_type:&quot;text/plain&quot;,<br/>
		  data: &quot;VGhpcyBpcyBhIGJhc2U2NCBlbmNvZGVkIHRleHQ=&quot;<br/>
	      }<br/>
	  }<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br/>
<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;var save_response = db.save(binAttDoc);<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;T(save_response.ok);<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;var before = db.info().disk_size;<br/>
<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;// Compact it.<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;T(db.compact().ok);<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;T(db.last_req.status == 202);<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;// compaction isn't instantaneous, loop until done<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;while (db.info().compact_running) {};<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;var after = db.info().disk_size;<br/>
<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;// Compaction should reduce the database slightly, but not<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;// orders of magnitude (unless attachments introduce sparseness)<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;T(after &gt; before * 0.1, &quot;database shrunk massively after compaction.&quot;);<br/>
<br/>
};

This patch changes the use of A &lt; B to couch_util:collate  which seems to fix the collation issue. It breaks a couple of other tests which need to be reviewed for correctness.<br/>
<br/>
The main issue is that using A &lt; B  fails for &lt;&lt;&quot;a&quot;&gt;&gt; and &lt;&lt;&quot;Z&quot;&gt;&gt;

Fixed.  If you try to replicate a DB to itself, the replication will proceed, but no checkpoints will be saved, and the logs will say<br/>
<br/>
&quot;checkpoint failure: conflict (are you replicating to yourself?)&quot;

When requesting a database that doesn't exist, the body is now:<br/>
<br/>
{&quot;error&quot;: &quot;not_found&quot;, &quot;reason&quot;: &quot;no_db_file&quot;}
